==Scots Gaelic==
===Etymology===
Possibly from ''[[maise]]'', "beauty"/"grace".
===Adjective===
'''maiseach'''
#[[beautiful]], [[lovely]], [[handsome]], [[fair]] (especially when applied to women) .
#:''"A [[rìbhinn]] maiseach Sgitheanach" ("O fair maiden from Skye").''

